				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">That was my info as well, Binnen.
<br />

<br />
In the past, I think pets would not have a delay higher than a set cap (think it was 30), but anything faster would work.  Also, their damage rating would not go below a certain level, thus maintaining their base performance; plus, they still had a damage cap similar to low level characters that prevented them from being able to do too much damage.
<br />

<br />
Not sure if this was indeed fact, nor if it is still that way, but it is one 'theory' that I had heard through my experiences in EQ.<br />_________________<br /><center><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3" color="purple"><b><i>Elder Riveni Chakravanti</i></b></font><br><font size="2" color="black">Vah Shir Feral Beastmistress<br>Member of Lodestar<br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=486142">Profile</a><br></font></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
